</p>
<p>Don't worry about calling the parent function, it's empty.</p>
<p>The <code>FormView</code> object that's passed to this method is the final, top-level <code>FormView</code>
object that represents the entire form. Now, check this out: use
<code>$view['funFact']-&gt;vars['help'] = </code> and then type a message, like, a nice fun
fact suggestion:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="eccbdaabe8">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
            <span class="fa fa-clipboard js-activate-clipboard" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Copy Code" data-placement="top"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="info">
